**Why retries break non-idempotent operations:**
Suppose a client POSTs a payment request and gets a network timeout. It retries. If the server processed the first request but the response was lost, the customer is charged twice. An idempotency key prevents this.

**Implementation pattern in ASP.NET Core:**
```csharp
[HttpPost("charges")]
public async Task<IActionResult> CreateCharge(
    [FromHeader(Name = "Idempotency-Key")] string idempotencyKey,
    [FromBody] ChargeRequest request)
{
    var cached = await _cache.GetAsync<ChargeResponse>(idempotencyKey);
    if (cached is not null) return Ok(cached);

    var result = await _paymentService.ChargeAsync(request);

    await _cache.SetAsync(idempotencyKey, result, TimeSpan.FromHours(24));
    return Ok(result);
}
```

**Message consumer (Azure Service Bus):**
```csharp
public async Task ProcessMessageAsync(ServiceBusReceivedMessage msg)
{
    var messageId = msg.MessageId;
    if (await _processedIds.ExistsAsync(messageId)) return; // already handled

    await HandleEventAsync(msg);
    await _processedIds.MarkAsync(messageId, TimeSpan.FromDays(7));
}
```

**Distributed caching for keys:** use Redis `SET key value EX 86400 NX` (SET if Not eXists) atomically to avoid race conditions where two identical requests arrive simultaneously.

code.snippet:
// Redis-backed idempotency middleware sketch
public async Task InvokeAsync(HttpContext ctx, IDistributedCache cache)
{
    if (!ctx.Request.Headers.TryGetValue("Idempotency-Key", out var key))
    {
        await _next(ctx);
        return;
    }

    var cached = await cache.GetStringAsync(key!);
    if (cached is not null)
    {
        ctx.Response.ContentType = "application/json";
        ctx.Response.StatusCode = 200;
        await ctx.Response.WriteAsync(cached);
        return;
    }

    // Capture response body for storage
    var originalBody = ctx.Response.Body;
    using var ms = new MemoryStream();
    ctx.Response.Body = ms;
    await _next(ctx);

    ms.Seek(0, SeekOrigin.Begin);
    var body = await new StreamReader(ms).ReadToEndAsync();
    await cache.SetStringAsync(key!, body,
        new DistributedCacheEntryOptions { AbsoluteExpirationRelativeToNow = TimeSpan.FromHours(24) });

    ms.Seek(0, SeekOrigin.Begin);
    await ms.CopyToAsync(originalBody);
}

